						<summary>

						<p>The basement of the Indranāthasvāmi temple, in front of the <hi rend="italic">nandimaṇḍapa.</hi></p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 13th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record that Paṟe Chennaya of Ghaṇḍīkōṭa attained salvation after paying homage to god Indrēśvaradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
